Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.63,0:04:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fe134}{\fsp0}{\fad(500,500)}{\pos(190,278)}{\fn方正准圆简体}{\bord0}{\fs20}{\c&H24EFFF&}宇宙大探索\n{\fs17}{\c&HFFFFFF&} 第四集
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.91,0:04:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That Sun...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.54,0:04:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,並不真的在那個位置\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it's not really there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.28,0:04:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽實際上升出地平線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It won't actually be above the horizon
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.25,0:04:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,是兩分鐘以後的事情\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for another two minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.75,0:04:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,日出只是個幻象\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The sunrise is an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.12,0:04:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,大氣層使射入的陽光發生了折射\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Earth's atmosphere bends the incoming rays of sunlight
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.92,0:04:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,就像鏡片和一杯水那樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}like a lens or a glass of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.42,0:05:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我們看到的只是地平線之上的投影\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So we see the image of the Sun projected above the horizon...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.09,0:05:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽本身還沒到達那個位置\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}before the physical Sun is actually there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.93,0:05:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我身後的太陽只是海市蜃樓\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That Sun behind me is a mirage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.60,0:05:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,就像那閃爍的圖像\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No more real than the shimmering image
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.70,0:05:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,漂浮在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that hovers in the distance
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.87,0:05:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,炎熱天氣下的沙漠遠方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}over a desert road on a hot day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.94,0:05:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,日光需要8分鐘才能達到地球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Sunlight takes about eight minutes to reach Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.94,0:05:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽離我們8光分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}so the Sun is eight light-minutes away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.21,0:05:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,對於太陽來說  我們只能看到它\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}From Earth, we can only ever see the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.98,0:05:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,8分鐘之前的樣子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as it was eight minutes ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.89,0:05:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,還有一件事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And another thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.29,0:05:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽並不是真的 升起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the Sun doesn't really "rise" at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.56,0:05:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,地球帶著我們一起旋轉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Earth turns and we turn with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.29,0:05:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,看上去也許不像  但是這個時候\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It may not look like it, but right at this moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.23,0:05:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我比飛機走的還快\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I'm moving faster than a jet plane
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.63,0:05:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,你也是  其他所有人都一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and so are you and everyone on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.13,0:05:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,當我看過去\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}While I'm at it,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.34,0:05:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,地平線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that horizon...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.64,0:05:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,並不真的存在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it's not really there at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.14,0:05:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,根本沒有邊緣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's no edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.47,0:05:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,地平線也只是一種幻象\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The horizon is just another illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.99,0:06:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,地球離最外圍的行星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The distance between Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.59,0:06:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,海王星的距離\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the outermost planet Neptune
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.70,0:06:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,隨著環日軌道而不同\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}varies as the planets orbit the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.20,0:06:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,平均來說  光要4個小時才能傳來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}On average, the light makes that trip in four hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.80,0:06:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,所以對我們來說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So for us on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.44,0:06:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我們看到的是4小時前海王星的樣子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the Neptune we see is always four hours in the past--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.34,0:06:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,距離 4光時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}four light-hours away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.01,0:06:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,但行星間的距離\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the distances to the planets,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.28,0:06:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,就算最遙遠的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}even the farthest one...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.95,0:06:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,相對星系間和恆星間的距離來說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are mere baby steps on a much grander scale
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.68,0:06:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,也只不過是微不足道的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the stars and galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.52,0:06:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,一旦我們離開太陽系\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}As soon as we leave the Sun's immediate neighborhood,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.03,0:06:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我們就需要把距離單位\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we need to change the unitive distance
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.86,0:06:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,從光時換到光年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from light-hours to light-years.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.03,0:06:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,光年是宇宙中的距離單位\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A light-year is the yardstick of the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.57,0:06:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,1光年將近10萬億公里\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A single one is nearly ten trillion kilometers,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.70,0:06:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,大約6萬億英里\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or about six trillion miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.37,0:06:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙距離單位中  就像1米或1英里那樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's a unitive distance, just like a meter or a mile.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.58,0:06:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,它是光線用1年時間可以穿越的距離長度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's the distance light travels in a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.88,0:07:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,離太陽最近的恆星  比鄰星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The nearest star to the Sun, Proxima Centauri,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.88,0:07:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}由天文學家羅伯特·因尼斯於1915年在南非發現
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.72,0:07:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,離地球的距離超過4光年一點點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is a little more than four light-years away from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.09,0:07:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,4光年有多遠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How far away is four light-years?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.32,0:07:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,NASA的旅行者探測器\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}NASA's Voyager spacecraft moves
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.72,0:07:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,速度超過每小時5萬6千公里\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at more than 56,000 kilometers an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.66,0:07:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,就算這麼驚人的速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Even at that astonishing speed, it would take Voyager
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.83,0:07:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,也需要超過8萬年  才能到達最近的恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}more than 80,000 years to reach the nearest star.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.51,0:07:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,昂宿星團的恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And the stars of the Pleiades cluster,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.51,0:07:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}一個大而明亮的疏散星團，位於金牛座，裸眼就可以輕易的看見
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.51,0:07:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,距離我們 400光年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}400 light-years away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.91,0:07:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,想像之舟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Ship of the Imagination
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.61,0:07:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,有著一種不同尋常的能力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is equipped with a highly unusual capability--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.91,0:07:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,獨一無二的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}one-of-a-kind, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.62,0:07:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,它能讓我們看到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It makes it possible for us to see what was happening
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.95,0:07:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,光從遙遠的恆星或星系發出\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when the light from a distant star or galaxy first set out
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.92,0:07:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,直到地球的情形\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on its long journey to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.26,0:07:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,400年前  光從昴宿星團出發時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When that light left the Pleiades, about 400 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.77,0:07:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,伽利略第一次使用望遠鏡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Galileo was taking his first look through a telescope.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.47,0:08:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,幾年後 他嘗試測算光的速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A few years later, he tried to measure the speed of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.47,0:08:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}讓甲乙兩人在夜裏相隔一段距離面對面站著，每人都拿一盞提燈。\n甲首先開燈，乙一看到甲的燈光立刻打開自己的燈。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.78,0:08:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}甲記下從自己開燈起到看到乙的燈光為止所經過的時間。\n然後用甲乙之間距離的兩倍去除以這個時間，就得到光的速度。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.11,0:08:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,但是沒有成功\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but he couldn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.94,0:08:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,他的計劃很高明  可惜當時的科技\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He had a very clever plan, but the technology of that era
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.81,0:08:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,還不能測量那麼快的速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}just wasn't good enough to measure the motion of anything
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.81,0:08:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,像光那麼快的速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that moves as fast as light.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.45,0:08:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我們從地球上觀察蟹狀星雲時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When we look at the Crab Nebula from Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.79,0:08:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我們看到的是更古老的過去\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we're seeing much farther back in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.79,0:08:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,蟹狀星雲曾是一顆巨大的恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Crab Nebula was once a giant star,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.29,0:08:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,質量比太陽大10倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}ten times the mass of the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.80,0:08:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,爆炸成為一顆超新星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}until it exploded in a supernova.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.63,0:08:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,它的中心是顆脈衝星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}At its heart is a pulsar,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.67,0:08:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,城市般大小的一顆坍塌星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a collapsed star the size of a city,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.67,0:08:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}中子星
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.14,0:08:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,每秒自轉30次\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}spinning 30 times a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.68,0:08:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,脈衝星的螺旋磁場\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This pulsar's whirling magnetic field
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.15,0:08:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,瘋狂地捲動 周圍的電子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}whips nearby electrons into a frenzy,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.25,0:08:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,將他們加速到接近光的速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}accelerating them to almost the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.32,0:08:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,他們發出藍色的光芒照亮超新星爆炸時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They shine with a blue glow that lights up the tendrils of gas
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.83,0:08:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,產生的氣態捲鬚\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}still unraveling from the supernova.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.33,0:08:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,蟹狀星雲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Crab Nebula
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.86,0:09:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,距離地球大約6500光年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is about 6,500 light-years from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.67,0:09:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,在某些宗教信仰中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}According to some beliefs,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.70,0:09:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,那是整個宇宙的年紀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that's the age of the whole universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.17,0:09:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,但如果宇宙只有6500歲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But if the universe were only 6,500 years old,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.84,0:09:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我們怎麼可能看到更遠的光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}how could we see the light from anything more distant
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.95,0:09:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,比蟹狀星雲還遠的光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}than the Crab Nebula?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.78,0:09:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,做不到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We couldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.78,0:09:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,那並沒有足夠的時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There wouldn't have been enough time for the light
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.69,0:09:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,讓光從距離超過6500光年的地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to get to Earth from anywhere farther away
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.35,0:09:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,傳來地球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}than 6,500 light-years in any direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.19,0:09:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,那點時間只夠光在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's just enough time for light to travel
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.79,0:09:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的銀河系中穿越很短的距離\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}through a tiny portion of our Milky Way galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.66,0:09:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,如果相信宇宙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To believe in a universe
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.90,0:09:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,只有6千到7千歲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as young as 6,000 or 7,000 years old
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.74,0:09:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,就是熄滅了銀河系中大部分的光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is to extinguish the light from most of the galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.81,0:09:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,更別提那些可觀測宇宙中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}not to mention the light from all the 100 billion
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.87,0:09:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,上千億星系發出的光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}other galaxies in the observable universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.44,0:10:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我們銀河系的中心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The center of our own galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.58,0:10:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,距離地球大約3萬光年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is about 30,000 light-years from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.78,0:10:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我們今天看到的光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The light we see today
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.75,0:10:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,從銀河系的核心出發時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}coming from the core of the Milky Way left there...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.25,0:10:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的遠古祖先找到了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when our ancestors were perfecting a way
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.19,0:10:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,超越死亡的方法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to vanquish death...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.86,0:10:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,使用繪畫的力量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by making art with the power
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.86,0:10:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,給予後世啟示\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to inspire those who would come long after they were gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.87,0:10:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,從闊邊帽星系傳來的光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The light we see coming from the Sombrero Galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.87,0:10:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}其擁有明亮且巨大的星系核\n尤其在赤道方向有一條由星際塵埃所形成的暗帶\n是攝影愛好者的必定拍攝對像之一
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.54,0:10:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,走了3千萬年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is 30 million years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.98,0:10:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,當光發出來時  我們的祖先還住在樹上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our ancestors were living in trees when that light started out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.45,0:11:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,他們大約5公斤重  還有長長的尾巴\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They weighed about five kilos and had long tails.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.62,0:11:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,但就算離我們3千萬光年之外\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But even 30 million light-years away
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.16,0:11:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,從宇宙中看 也不過就在我們的後院\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is still in our own cosmic backyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.96,0:11:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,那個星系屬於後發座星系團\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That galaxy is part of the Coma Cluster,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.30,0:11:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,3億2千萬光年之遙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}320 million light-years away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.57,0:11:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,當這裏的光出發時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What was going on back home
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.47,0:11:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,當時的地球又是怎樣的呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when the light you are seeing began its trip to Earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.48,0:11:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有我們熟悉的大陸  海洋  河流\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No familiar continents, oceans or rivers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.75,0:11:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的遠古祖先剛剛從水中登上陸地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our distant ancestors were just leaving the water for the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.99,0:11:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,很古老的光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's pretty old light,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.82,0:11:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,但遠不是 我們能看到的 最古老的光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but not nearly the oldest light we can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.03,0:11:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,最古老的光已經很微弱了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The oldest light is very faint,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.26,0:11:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,暗夜中虛弱的鬼魂\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a pale ghost in the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.43,0:11:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,看到圓圈中的紅點嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}See that red blob inside the circle?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.50,0:11:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,那是我們能見的最古老星系之一\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's one of the oldest galaxies we've ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.00,0:11:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,你看到的是134億歲高齡的星光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You're looking at 13.4-billion year-old starlight
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.04,0:12:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,通過哈勃太空望遠鏡捕捉到的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as captured by the Hubble space telescope.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.79,0:12:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,它來自第一代的星星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's coming from the very first generation of stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.62,0:12:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,當時的地球什麼情況\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What was happening on Earth back then?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.19,0:12:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,完全沒情況\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Absolutely nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.36,0:12:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,當時 沒有地球 沒有太陽 沒有銀河系\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There was no Earth, no Sun, no Milky Way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.03,0:12:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,它們都是幾十億年後才誕生的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They would not come to be for billions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.04,0:12:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,當我們看向宇宙的更深處\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When we try to look even farther into the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.04,0:12:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,好像已經到了宇宙的盡頭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we come to what appears to be the end of space...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.38,0:12:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,但事實上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.25,0:12:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,這是時間的開始\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it's the beginning of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.34,0:12:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,地球向下拉著我們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Earth pulls on us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.94,0:12:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我們不斷地反抗引力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our lives are a relentless struggle with gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.43,0:13:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,這個小女孩用盡全力要爬出\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That little girl is trying her best to climb out
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.76,0:13:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,引力的包圍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of a gravitational well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.03,0:13:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,從第一次嘗試站立到最後的倒下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}From our first efforts to stand to our final surrender,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.94,0:13:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,我們一直在努力克服地心引力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we are struggling to overcome the Earth's pull.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.44,0:13:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,我們在重力場中誕生  生活  過世\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We are born, live and die in a force field--
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.38,0:13:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,重力場幾乎和宇宙本身一樣的古老\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}one that is almost as old as the universe itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.82,0:13:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,有多古老\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And how old is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.45,0:13:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,為了想像宇宙的138億年歲月\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To visualize the 13.8 billion year age of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.06,0:13:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我們把所有的宇宙時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we've compressed all of cosmic time
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.62,0:13:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,壓縮在一份單張的年歷中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into a single year-at-a-glance calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.13,0:13:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,現在是12月31號的午夜\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Midnight on December 31 is this very moment right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.96,0:13:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,而1月1號就是時間的開始\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And January 1 is the beginning of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.00,0:13:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,看到那耀眼的煙霧嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}See that glowing fog out there?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.40,0:13:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,它是大爆炸遺留下的輻射物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's radiation left over from the Big Bang,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.57,0:13:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,在138億年前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the explosion that made the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.58,0:13:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,大爆炸創造了宇宙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}13.8 billion years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.91,0:14:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,現在 我們站在已知空間和時間的邊緣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Right now, we're at the very edge of known space and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.59,0:14:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,那麼 大爆炸之前是什麼樣子呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So what happened before the Big Bang?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.82,0:14:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,沒人知道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Nobody knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.49,0:14:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有絲毫關於那之前的證據\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No evidence survives from before that moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.33,0:14:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我們有一些很瘋狂的猜想\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We've got some pretty crazy ideas
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.16,0:14:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,是關於宇宙的來源\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}about where the universe came from,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.66,0:14:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我們以後會提到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which we'll get to, in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.67,0:14:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我們在宇宙的什麼位置\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Where are we in the universe?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.60,0:14:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,就在正中心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}At the very center.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.71,0:14:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,在已知宇宙中 每個人都覺得自己很特殊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In the observed universe, everyone gets to feel special.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.68,0:14:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,不論你身處哪個星系\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No matter which galaxy you happen to live in,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.55,0:14:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,當你看向宇宙時  你會發現自己\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when you look out to the universe, you'll find yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.68,0:14:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,身處宇宙地平線的中心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at the center of the cosmic horizon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.02,0:14:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,但這不過是個錯覺\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But this is just an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.02,0:14:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,實際上  沒有中心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In reality, there is no center,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.89,0:14:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙地平線和海上的地平線 一樣不真實\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the cosmic horizon is no more real than the horizon at sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.23,0:14:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,這是因為 在有起始時間的宇宙中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's what you get when you have a finite speed of light
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.07,0:14:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,光速是有限的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in a universe that had a beginning in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.37,0:15:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,大爆炸後的幾億年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A few hundred million years after the Big Bang,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.38,0:15:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,大量的氫氣和氦氣雲團\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}vast clouds of hydrogen and helium condensed
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.55,0:15:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,凝結成最初的恆星和星系\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into the first stars and galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.82,0:15:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,有了這些新的光源\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}With these new sources of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.38,0:15:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙漫長的黑暗時代從此終結\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the long dark ages of the universe ended.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.42,0:15:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,隨著宇宙的不斷膨脹\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}As space continued to expand,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.99,0:15:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙進化的規模變得更加宏大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}cosmic evolution unfolded on grander scales.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.73,0:15:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,最初的星星死亡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}As the first generation of stars died,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.06,0:15:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,他們將較重的元素散佈在宇宙中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they seeded space with heavier elements,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.40,0:15:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,使得行星的形成 成為可能\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}making possible the formation of planets,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.07,0:15:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,最終 生命的形成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and ultimately, life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.24,0:15:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,大爆炸形成了物質和能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Matter and energy were formed in the Big Bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.78,0:15:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,還有\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But that's not all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.25,0:15:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,創造了空間和時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Space and time were created, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.75,0:15:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,還有束縛所有物質的力量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and all the forces that bind matter together,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.08,0:15:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,包括 重力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}including gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.62,0:15:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,牛頓發現了一個數學定律\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Isaac Newton discovered a mathematical law
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.02,0:15:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,可以形容重力的運作機制\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that describes how gravity works.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.42,0:15:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,他可以用它解釋行星間的運動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}With that law, he could explain the motions of the planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.76,0:15:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,100多年後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}More than 100 years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.76,0:15:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,威廉·赫歇爾 意識到 那還不是全部\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}William Herschel realized gravity could do much more.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.94,0:16:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,約翰 你能保守秘密嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}John, can you keep a secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.28,0:16:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,可以 父親\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Yes, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.11,0:16:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我有了一個發現  還沒告訴過任何人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I've made a discovery and have yet to tell another soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.95,0:16:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上的地心引力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The gravity that holds us to the Earth--
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.15,0:16:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,同樣是牛頓發現的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the same gravity that Newton showed
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.12,0:16:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,將行星保持在軌道上的引力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}keeps the planets in their orbits--
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.06,0:16:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我發現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I've discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.63,0:16:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,也同樣適用於 相隔遙遠的恆星們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that it also rules the distant stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.66,0:16:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,爹  你咋知道的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Father... but how can you know this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.97,0:16:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,你能找到獅子座嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Can you find the constellation of the Lion?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.14,0:16:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,在那\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.51,0:16:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,幹得好\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Well done.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.84,0:16:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,你能找到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Can you now find the star
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.48,0:16:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,連接頭部和身體的那顆星嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that joins the Lion's head to his body?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.82,0:16:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,那個\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.15,0:16:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,那其實是兩顆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That star is really two stars
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.52,0:16:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,靠的很近 看上去就像一顆\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}so close together that they appear to be one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.52,0:16:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我用望遠鏡觀察了很久\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I've been watching them through my telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.16,0:17:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,你出生很久前就開始了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}since long before you were born.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.50,0:17:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,他們非常緩慢的 圍繞相互移動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They dance around each other very slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.43,0:17:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,遠比行星繞恆星運動的慢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}More slowly than any planet moves around the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.67,0:17:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我們今晚看到的許多星星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Many of the stars we see tonight,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.34,0:17:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,可能大部分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}perhaps most of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.34,0:17:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,按照看不見的規律移動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}dance with invisible partners.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.95,0:17:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,萬有引力這個大帝國統治著所有的星球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Gravity's empire governs all the heavens.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.70,0:17:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,1個世紀前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A century earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.06,0:17:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,艾薩克·牛頓備受困擾\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Isaac Newton had been haunted
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.97,0:17:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,他也找不到引力的作用機制\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by the same absence of a mechanism for gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.04,0:17:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,相距甚遠的物體 如何相互影響\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How could distant bodies affect each other
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.64,0:17:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,不用接觸就相互影響\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}across empty space without actually touching?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.41,0:17:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,這個他稱之為 超距作用 的問題困擾著他\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This "action at a distance," as he called it, baffled him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.38,0:17:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,19世紀 邁克爾·法拉第（電學之父）發現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In the 19th century, Michael Faraday discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.38,0:17:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}電學之父
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.88,0:17:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我們被不可見的力場包圍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that we were surrounded by invisible fields of force
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.99,0:18:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,這解釋了引力的運作機制\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that explained how gravity works.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.72,0:18:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,蘋果和地球 並沒有發生接觸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The apple and the Earth don't touch each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.33,0:18:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,但是他們之間的力場產生了接觸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but the fields between them do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.00,0:18:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,他想像引力產生的線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He imagined those lines of gravitational force
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.57,0:18:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,從每一個物體 向太空中輻射\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}radiating out into space from every massive body--
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.60,0:18:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,地球 月亮 太陽  所有的一切\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the Earth, the Moon, the Sun, everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.91,0:18:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是那個困擾牛頓的問題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Here was the answer to that question
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.78,0:18:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,的答案\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that had stumped Newton.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.41,0:18:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,1985年 詹姆斯·克拉克·麥克斯韋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In 1865, James Clerk Maxwell translated Faraday's idea
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.18,0:18:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,把法拉第關於電磁場的理論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}about fields of electricity and magnetism
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.79,0:18:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,轉化成了數學公式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into mathematical laws.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.59,0:18:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,他發現這些磁場 電場都以波的形式在空間中移動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He discovered that these fields move through space in waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.63,0:18:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,當他計算它們的移動速度時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When he calculated how fast they move,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.26,0:18:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,結果是 光的速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it turned out to be the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.27,0:18:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我們才發現了  宇宙這個大掛毯上的線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We were beginning to discover the threads of the cosmic tapestry,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.10,0:18:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,但是我們還無法 看出豐富的圖案\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but we were not yet able to discern the rich pattern
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.21,0:18:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,時間 光 空間 重力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that time, light, space and gravity weave.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.28,0:18:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,阿爾伯特·愛因斯坦 在柏林\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}As Albert Einstein worked in Berlin
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.81,0:18:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,研究他的引力理論時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on his theory of gravity,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.65,0:19:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,牆上掛了這3位前輩的頭像\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he kept the portraits of these three men before him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.38,0:19:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,他知道他的成就  建立在他們的基礎上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He knew he was standing on their shoulders.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.75,0:19:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,多年前  少年時  他有過一個頓悟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Years before, as a teenager, he had an insight
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.76,0:19:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,如同前輩們的理論那般驚天動地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that was as Earth-shaking as any idea of theirs.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.43,0:19:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,那年夏天\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And it happened one summer
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.13,0:19:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,他在意大利遐想時的頓悟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}while he was daydreaming in Italy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.70,0:19:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,1895年的夏天\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In the summer of 1895,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.54,0:19:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,他父親在德國的生意失敗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Einstein's father's business in Germany had failed,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.37,0:19:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,全家搬到了意大利北部\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the family had moved here to northern Italy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.88,0:19:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,小愛因斯坦喜歡在這些路上散步\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Young Einstein loved wandering these roads
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.71,0:19:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,讓他的思維隨意發散\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and giving his mind free rein to explore.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.55,0:19:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,這裏有著某些永恆的東西\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's something timeless about this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.95,0:19:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,和愛因斯坦最初的遐想時相比\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Nothing here has really changed
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.56,0:19:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,基本沒什麼變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}since the time of Einstein's early daydreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.90,0:19:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,一天 他想到了光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}One day, he began to think about light
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.23,0:19:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,還有光速\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and how fast it travels.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.74,0:20:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,日常生活中 我們總是測量物體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In everyday life, we always measure the speed
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.97,0:20:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,相對於其他物體的移動速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of a moving object with respect to something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.64,0:20:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,假設其他物體沒有移動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Something that's presumably not moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.91,0:20:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙中的其他物體沒有運動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Something in the cosmos that's not in motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.01,0:20:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,比方說  我的速度大約每小時10公里\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For example, I'm moving about ten kilometers per hour
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.85,0:20:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,相對於地面而言\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}relative to the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.29,0:20:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,但我之前提過  大地也在運動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But as I mentioned earlier, the ground is moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.36,0:20:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,地球的轉速超過每小時1600公里\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Earth is turning at more than 1,600 kilometers per hour
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.76,0:20:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,在環日軌道上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}while it orbits the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.53,0:20:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,速度超過每小時10萬公里\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at more than 100,000 kilometers per hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.37,0:20:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,並且太陽系在銀河系中運行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And the Sun is moving through the galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.77,0:20:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,約為每小時90萬公里
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.77,0:20:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,每小時50萬英里的速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at a half a million miles per hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.84,0:20:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,銀河系在宇宙中運行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And the Milky Way is moving through the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.04,0:20:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}實際約為216萬公里
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.04,0:20:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,速度將近每小時150萬英里\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at nearly one and a half million miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.14,0:20:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙中沒有不動的地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There is no fixed place in the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.31,0:20:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,一切都在運動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}All of nature is in motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.15,0:20:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,對小愛因斯坦來說  也是很難想像出\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was hard even for the young Einstein
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.29,0:20:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,一個絕對的標準\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to imagine some absolute standard
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.39,0:20:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,用來衡量所有這些相對的運動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to measure all those relative motions against.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.84,0:21:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,就是這本書\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is the very book
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.47,0:21:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,啟發了少年愛因斯坦\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that inspired Einstein as a young boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.51,0:21:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,給了他一本書  改變了這個世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Give a kid a book and you change the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.68,0:21:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,某種程度上  改變了這個宇宙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In a way, even the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.02,0:21:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,看這裏  第一頁\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Look at this-- the very first page,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.59,0:21:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,它描述了令人驚訝的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it describes the astonishing speed
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.49,0:21:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,電流通過電線的速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of electricity through wires
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.26,0:21:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,光穿過宇宙的速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and light through space.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.86,0:21:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,愛因斯坦記得他小時候從這本書裏學到的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Einstein remembered what he'd learned as a child from this book
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.50,0:21:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,或許 最初 就在這裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and perhaps, for the first time, right here,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.93,0:21:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,想像著這個世界將會如何\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}wondered what the world would look like
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.60,0:21:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,如果可以用光速運動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}if you could travel at the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.34,0:21:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,愛因斯坦越想\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The more Einstein thought about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.84,0:21:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,越覺得困惑\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the more troubled he became.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.75,0:21:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你想像以光速運動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If you imagine traveling at the speed of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.08,0:21:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,各個方面都充滿了矛盾\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}paradoxes seem to pop up everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.95,0:21:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,愛因斯坦驚訝的發現 如此眾多的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Einstein was shocked to realize that so much
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.76,0:22:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,即使是被最偉大的權威人士\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of what had been uncritically accepted as truth
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.79,0:22:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,無條件接受的真理\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by even the greatest authorities on the subject
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.36,0:22:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,竟是大錯特錯\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was just plain wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.60,0:22:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,以高速運動時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When traveling at high speeds,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.97,0:22:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,必須遵守一些特定的規則\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}there are certain rules which must be obeyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.94,0:22:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,愛因斯坦稱之為 相對性原理\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Einstein called these rules "The Principles of Relativity."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.71,0:22:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,想像剛才那位呼嘯而過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Imagine that young woman who just blew past us
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.41,0:22:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,騎摩托的年輕女士\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on the motorbike,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.88,0:22:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,想像她騎車穿行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}imagine she was riding her bike
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.38,0:22:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,在宇宙中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}through the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.41,0:22:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,從移動的物體上發出的光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Light from a moving object travels
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.05,0:22:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,不論物體是靜止還是移動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at the same speed, no matter whether the object
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.05,0:22:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,速度都是一樣的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is at rest or in motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.96,0:22:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,她的速度並不會增加光的速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Her speed is not added to the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.89,0:22:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,從她的摩托車發出的光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The light from her motorbike
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.73,0:22:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,依然是光的速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}still travels at the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.93,0:22:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,大自然的諭旨\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Nature commands,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.73,0:22:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,汝不可超越光速\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}"Thou shalt not add my speed to the speed of light."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.57,0:22:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,同樣 沒有物質\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Also, no material object
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.14,0:22:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,傳播速度可以達到或者超過光速\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}can travel at or faster than the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.74,0:22:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,物理上 沒有什麼可以阻止你\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's nothing in physics that prevents you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.84,0:22:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,隨心所欲地接近光的速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from traveling as close to the speed of light as you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.45,0:22:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,99.9%的光速 沒問題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}99.9% of the speed of light is just fine,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.12,0:23:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,但是無論你怎麼努力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but no matter how hard you try,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.59,0:23:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,都無法得到 最後的那個百分點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}you never gain that last decimal point.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.09,0:23:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,以現實的邏輯一致性來說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For reality to be logically consistent,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.92,0:23:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,必然存在一個宇宙速度極限\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}there must be a cosmic speed limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.77,0:23:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,鞭子發出的聲音是因為\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The crack of that whip is due to its tip
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.27,0:23:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,鞭頭的移動速度超過了聲速\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}moving faster than the speed of sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.27,0:23:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,產生了衝擊波\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It makes a shockwave,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.11,0:23:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,例如這個在意大利鄉村的 一個小小的音爆\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a mini sonic boom, in the Italian countryside.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.31,0:23:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,打雷也是一樣的道理\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A thunderclap works the same way,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.51,0:23:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,還有超音速飛機掠過時的聲音\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and so does the sound of a passing supersonic jet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.65,0:23:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,那為什麼光速\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So why is the speed of light
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.99,0:23:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,比音速更難超越\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}any more a barrier than the speed of sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.16,0:23:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,答案是 不僅僅光速\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The answer is not just that light travels
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.89,0:23:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,比音速快100萬倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}about a million times faster than sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.13,0:23:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,也因為 這不僅是一個工程學問題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And it's not merely an engineering problem,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.56,0:23:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,像建造首架超音速飛機那種\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}like building the first supersonic jet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.13,0:23:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,光障\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Instead, the light barrier
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.53,0:23:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,是自然的基本定律\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is a fundamental law of nature,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.47,0:23:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,就像萬有引力一樣基本\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as basic as gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.34,0:23:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,愛因斯坦為這個世界設定了絕對的準則\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Einstein found his absolute framework for the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.64,0:23:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,這給了宇宙運動中的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}this sturdy pillar among all the relative motions
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.71,0:24:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,所有相對運動強有力的支持\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}within the motions of the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.41,0:24:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,光速就是那麼快\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Light travels just as fast,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.21,0:24:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,無論光源移動的快慢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}no matter how fast or slow its source is moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.38,0:24:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,相對其他任何東西 光速是恆定的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Speed of light is constant, relative to everything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.39,0:24:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有什麼可以追上光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Nothing can ever catch up with light.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.86,0:24:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,自然定律的偉大就是在於\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The thing about the laws of nature
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.00,0:24:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,他們無懈可擊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is that they're unbreakable.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.90,0:24:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,物理學家的工作就是發現這些定律\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The job of physicists is to discover these commandments,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.90,0:24:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,定律不隨文化的不同而改變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the ones that do not vary from culture to culture
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.87,0:24:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,也不隨時間而改變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or time to time
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.54,0:24:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,放之宇宙而皆准\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and hold true throughout the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.67,0:24:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是為何  如同愛因斯坦指出的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's why, as Einstein showed,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.78,0:24:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,接近光速時就出問題了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}funny things happen close to the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.62,0:24:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,以接近光速的速度旅行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Traveling close to the speed of light
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.55,0:24:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,就像是長生不老藥\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is kind of an elixir of life
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.12,0:24:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的生物鐘慢下來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}because your biological clock slows down
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.13,0:24:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,相對於其他人來說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}relative to those you leave behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.29,0:24:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,這種現象或許可以為我們人類\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This phenomenon may provide us humans,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.96,0:24:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,只能活1個世紀左右的人類\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}who only live for a century or so,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.03,0:24:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,提供一個可行的恆星間旅行的方案\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a practical means to travel to the stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.47,0:24:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,時空魔法大戲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where the magic show of spacetime
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.64,0:25:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,精彩紛呈\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}really gets crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.59,0:25:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,19世紀的天文學家 威廉·赫歇爾\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The 19th-century astronomer William Herschel
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.52,0:25:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,喜歡和他的兒子約翰\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}loved to share the wonders of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.83,0:25:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,分享宇宙中的奇跡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with his son John.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.67,0:25:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我有個朋友 一個很聰明的傢伙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I once had a friend, very clever fellow,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.11,0:25:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,天文學家 也是裏茲的牧師\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}an astronomer and a parson at Leeds,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.28,0:25:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,叫 約翰·米切爾\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by the name of John Michell.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.01,0:25:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,你還是嬰兒時 他就過世了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Poor man died when you were a babe,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.62,0:25:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,願他安息\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}God rest his soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.55,0:25:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,他堅信有些星星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He held that some stars
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.62,0:25:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,雖然看不到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are invisible.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.62,0:25:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,卻確實存在 但是我們永遠無法看到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They really exist, but we shall never see them.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.96,0:25:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,米切爾叫他們 「暗星」\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}"Dark stars," Michell called them.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.06,0:25:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,恕我直言 父親\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}With all due respect, Father,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.20,0:26:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,你的朋友肯定弄錯了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}surely your friend was mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.80,0:26:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,如果沒人能看到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If no one can see them,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.47,0:26:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我們怎麼能知道它們確實存在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}then how can we possibly know they exist?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.81,0:26:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,你看到留下腳印的人了嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Did you see the man who left those footprints, John?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.31,0:26:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,沒 怎麼了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Why, no, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.81,0:26:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,我沒看到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I did not.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.81,0:26:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,但你知道他們確實存在 不是嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But do you know that he exists?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.67,0:26:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,約翰 米切爾是最偉大的科學家之一\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}John Michell is one of the greatest scientists
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.57,0:26:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,你可能從沒聽說過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}you've probably never heard of.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.94,0:26:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,他生活工作於18世紀的英格蘭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He lived and worked in England in the 18th century.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.58,0:26:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,現在也沒有他的畫像存世\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If he ever sat for a portrait, it no longer exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.28,0:26:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,有人曾經形容他\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He was once described by an acquaintance
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.78,0:26:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,胖胖的黝黑小矮人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as "a short little man, of black complexion, and fat."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.02,0:26:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,米切爾設想一個巨大的恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Michell imagined a star so big,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.79,0:26:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,質量巨大到 即使光線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}so massive, that nothing, not even light,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.29,0:27:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,也無法逃離它的重力吸引\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}could escape its gravitational grip.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.86,0:27:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,你能找到暗星嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Can you find the dark star?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.86,0:27:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}暗星主要由超中性子構成 並通過暗物質和正物質的湮滅釋放能量
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.80,0:27:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,你無法用肉眼直接看見它\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You can't see it with your eyes, not directly,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.70,0:27:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,但在宇宙這個沙灘上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but it may leave a kind of footprint
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.20,0:27:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,它可能留下某種足跡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on the cosmic shore.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.21,0:27:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,米切爾認為因為他們巨大的引力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Michell realized that we might be able to detect
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.64,0:27:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,使得我們或許可以偵測到他們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}some of these dark stars because of their extreme gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.04,0:27:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,如果一個暗星 碰巧伴隨著一個\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If one happened to be near
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.45,0:27:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,稍小些 會發光的星星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a smaller, luminous companion star,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.72,0:27:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,那顆星星以緊密的軌道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that star would appear to travel in a tight orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.78,0:27:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,環繞著 看不見的東西運行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}around nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.65,0:27:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,即使我們看不到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Even though we can't see it,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.16,0:27:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我們也知道 有個質量超級巨大的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we know something with a lot of mass
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.89,0:27:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,東西在那裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}has to be right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.56,0:27:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,暗星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A dark star,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.06,0:27:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,或者叫 黑洞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or what today we call a black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.00,0:27:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,黑洞長什麼樣子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What does a black hole look like
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.73,0:27:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,它的裏面是什麼樣子的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and what would it be like inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.90,0:27:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我們以後會提到  但是首先\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We'll get there, but first,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.24,0:27:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,讓我們先在我的家鄉稍作休息\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}let's make a pit stop in my hometown,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.58,0:27:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,紐約\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}New York City,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.81,0:27:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,這地方在我來看\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where it's always seemed to me
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.18,0:27:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,所有的一切都在不停地運動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that everything is in constant motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.25,0:27:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我在這裏住了大半輩子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I've lived here most of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.98,0:27:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,總有新鮮事物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's always something new to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.09,0:28:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,但有一樣從來不變 重力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But one thing never changes-- gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.92,0:28:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,重力在過去的45億年間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Gravity on Earth has been the same
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.99,0:28:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,一直保持不變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for the past four and a half billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.43,0:28:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,如果 今天 我們可以改變它\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But what if, today, we could alter it?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.60,0:28:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,重力受時空影響\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Gravity is a distortion
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.43,0:28:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,會發生畸變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the shape of spacetime
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.43,0:28:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,如同愛因斯坦提出的理論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as Einstein showed.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.44,0:28:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,空間可以膨脹和收縮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Space can expand and contract
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.34,0:28:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至無限彎曲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and warp without limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.45,0:28:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,如果地球的體積和密度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If the Earth's size or density
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.78,0:28:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,有細微的不同\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}were even a little different,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.28,0:28:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,它的重力也會不同\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}its gravity would be, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.12,0:28:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,有無限的可能性\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's an infinite range of possibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.19,0:28:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,紐約人在這裏感受到的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}New Yorkers feel right at home
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.06,0:28:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,重力單位\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the gravitational pull of the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.62,0:28:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我們稱為 1g\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}called "one g."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.03,0:28:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,假設我們取消一條街上的重力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Suppose we turn off the gravity on one of its streets.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.81,0:28:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,運動中的人和物體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}People and objects that were already in motion
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.74,0:28:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,就會向上飛去\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are launched into flight.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.92,0:29:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我把重力加大到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now what if I turn the gravity up
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.32,0:29:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,比方說 8或者9g\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14} to, say, eight or nine g's?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.89,0:29:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,和諧起見\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Out of compassion,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.43,0:29:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,把人拿開\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}let's evacuate the area.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.06,0:29:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,這個重力和戰鬥機飛行員\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is about the same g-force
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.83,0:29:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,高速轉彎時承受的重力相當\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that a fighter pilot in a high-speed turn would feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.60,0:29:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,幾分鐘內 還不會使你受傷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A few minutes of this wouldn't hurt you,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.40,0:29:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,但是絕不會舒服\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but it wouldn't be comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.01,0:29:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,在10萬g時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}At 100,000 g's,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.68,0:29:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,消防栓也被自身的重量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}even fire hydrants become crushed
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.61,0:29:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,壓扁了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by their own enormous weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.25,0:29:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,而當達到幾百萬g\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But at millions of g's,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.02,0:29:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,光線也會被拉彎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}even light bows to gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.75,0:29:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,光線依然保持恆速\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The light still moves at its constant speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.35,0:29:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,但它無法逃逸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but it cannot escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.36,0:29:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,米切爾說的暗星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Michell's dark star...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.63,0:29:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我們稱為黑洞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}our black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.86,0:29:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,最近的一個 或許比想像的要近\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And the nearest one may be closer than you think.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.89,0:30:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,不是每個恆星都會變成黑洞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Not every star can become a black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.49,0:30:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,只有千分之一的質量足夠大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Only about one in a thousand is massive enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.54,0:30:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,最近的一個 可能距離地球不到100光年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The nearest one could be within 100 light years of Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.85,0:30:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,黑洞不是科幻小說裏的宇宙吸塵器\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Black holes aren't the mythic cosmic vacuum cleaners of science fiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.14,0:30:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,它們不會到處吞噬\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They don't go around gobbling up unsuspecting worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.98,0:30:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,你得去找它們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You've got to come to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.82,0:30:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,但是如果你去了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But if you do,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.42,0:30:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,可就是有去無回\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it might be the last thing you ever see.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.02,0:30:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,剛才那是我們在抵抗上百萬g的重力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That was us resisting a few million g's of gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.76,0:30:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,別忘了 那傢伙可以吞噬光線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Don't forget, that thing swallows light.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.20,0:30:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我們不能靠的太近\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We'll keep our distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.54,0:30:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,當巨大的恆星消耗完它們的核燃料\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When giant stars exhaust their nuclear fuel,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.37,0:30:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,他們不再保持高溫\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they can no longer stay hot enough
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.04,0:30:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,以抵消自身向內的引力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to fend off the inward pull of their own gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.84,0:30:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,質量最大的恆星塌陷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The most massive stars collapse into darkness,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.61,0:30:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有光亮 只留下重力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}leaving only their gravity behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.78,0:30:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,這個黑洞將一個超巨星的萎縮的屍體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This black hole enshrouds the shrunken corpse
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.29,0:30:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,隱藏其中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of a supergiant star.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.05,0:30:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,恆星本身可能萎縮到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The star itself has shriveled into something
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.19,0:31:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,比黑洞還小\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}even smaller than this darkness,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.39,0:31:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,只有64公里寬\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}only 64 kilometers wide.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.40,0:31:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,這是發現的第一個黑洞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is the first black hole ever discovered--
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.63,0:31:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,天鵝座X-1\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Cygnus X-1.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.90,0:31:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我們在地球上是怎麼發現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How did we on Earth ever find something
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.30,0:31:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,這麼小 這麼暗 這麼遠的 東西\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}so small and dark and far away?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.37,0:31:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我們通過另一種光 X光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We looked at it in another kind of light. X-rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.71,0:31:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,X光中 我們看不到藍色的星星了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In X-ray light, we lost sight of the blue star
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.48,0:31:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,因為它的表面溫度只有微溫的3萬度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}because its surface is a tepid 30,000 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.15,0:31:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,而黑洞周圍的氣體圓盤\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the disk of gas around the black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.76,0:31:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,在X光中發出耀眼的光芒 溫度高達1億度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}glowed brilliantly in X-rays at 100 million degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.59,0:31:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,如同威廉·赫歇爾所發現的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}As William Herschel discovered,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.43,0:31:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,很多恆星都有親密的小夥伴  組成聯星系統\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}many stars have close companions forming a binary star system.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.17,0:31:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,但如果其中一個異常巨大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But if one member of such a pair is enormous
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.44,0:31:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,另一個比較小\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the other is compact,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.40,0:31:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,小的這個可以吞噬它兄弟的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the smaller star can drain and consume the atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.91,0:31:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,大氣層\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of its larger sibling.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.34,0:31:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,這種神經病關係可以持續幾百萬年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This neurotic relationship can last for millions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.61,0:32:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,較大恆星的大氣層被抽到熾熱耀眼的吸積盤上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The atmosphere of the larger star was being siphoned onto
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.62,0:32:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,吸積盤不停自轉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a glowing hot accretion disk that revolves around
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.45,0:32:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,並且漩渦式的進入黑洞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and spirals into a black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.52,0:32:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,勢不可擋的重力不斷加速藍色星星的氣體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The overwhelming gravity was accelerating the blue star's gas
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.13,0:32:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,將其捲入死亡漩渦\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into a death spiral,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.60,0:32:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,跨過時空的界限\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}crossing the spacetime boundary,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.37,0:32:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,一去不復返\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}never to be seen again.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.97,0:32:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,這至關重要的界限將黑洞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The fateful boundary that separates a black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.44,0:32:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,與宇宙的其他部分隔離開  被稱為 事件視界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from the rest of the universe is called an event horizon.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.94,0:32:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,在我們看來 吸積盤中的物質\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}From our point of view, the substance in the disk
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.81,0:32:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,在靠近視界時慢下來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}slows down as it approaches the event horizon,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.15,0:32:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,但絕不接觸它\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}never quite reaching it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.62,0:32:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你站在大氣漩渦上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But if you were riding on that spiraling gas--
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.22,0:32:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我並不建議這麼做\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and I don't advise it--
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.05,0:32:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,幾秒鐘就會越過事件視界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}you would sail past the event horizon in a matter of seconds
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.06,0:32:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,進入到 從沒人回來的 未知國度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into the undiscovered country from which no traveler returns.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.24,0:32:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我們搜索了幾十個星系的中心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We have searched the hearts of dozens of galaxies,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.14,0:32:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,在每個裏面都能找到 一個質量超級大的黑洞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and in every case, we have found a super-massive black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.31,0:33:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的銀河系也不例外\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our own galaxy is no exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.75,0:33:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,最靠近銀河系中心的恆星運動的速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The stars nearest the center of our galaxy whip around
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.69,0:33:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,超過每小時4千萬公里\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at more than 40 million kilometers an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.92,0:33:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,他們怎麼會運動的這麼快\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What could make them move so fast?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.76,0:33:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,唯一合理的解釋是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The only logical explanation
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.50,0:33:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,銀河系中央存在著\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is that something with the mass
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.86,0:33:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,質量等於4百萬個太陽的物體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of four million suns lies at the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.37,0:33:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,這4百萬個太陽發出的光去哪裏了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So where's the blazing light of four million suns?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.87,0:33:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,既然我們看不見\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Since we can't see it,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.34,0:33:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,它一定是被禁錮在黑洞裏了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it must be imprisoned inside a black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.55,0:33:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,地球離得很遠 很安全\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Earth is far enough away to be perfectly safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.79,0:33:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,其他的世界或許沒有這麼幸運\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Other worlds might not be so lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.29,0:33:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你能穿過事件視界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If you somehow survived the perilous journey
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.96,0:33:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,卻還活著\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}across the event horizon,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.80,0:33:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以回頭看\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}you'd be able to look back out
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.36,0:33:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙的整部未來史都會\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and see the entire future history of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.37,0:33:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,展現在你眼前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}unfold before your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.41,0:34:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,怎麼會的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.97,0:34:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,因為 時空受到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Because when spacetime is warped
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.74,0:34:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,黑洞的極度重力影響而扭曲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by the extreme gravity of a black hole,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.15,0:34:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,時間被拉伸至極致\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}time is stretched to the limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.48,0:34:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,但你面前會是何種景象呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But what would be in front of you?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.82,0:34:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我提前警告你\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Before we go there, I should warn you
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.49,0:34:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我們說的是未經涉足過的科學領域\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that we're entering uncharted scientific territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.33,0:34:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,那裏可能有我們未知的物理定律\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For all we know, there may be undiscovered laws of physics
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.26,0:34:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,支配著黑洞中央的事情\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that govern events at the center of a black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.00,0:34:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,在下一個愛因斯坦出現前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But until the next Einstein comes along,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.44,0:34:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我們來做個思想實驗吧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}let's perform a thought experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.41,0:34:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,18世紀的約翰 米切爾\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's how John Michell first imagined dark stars
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.68,0:34:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,就是靠它想像出 暗星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the 18th century,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.85,0:34:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,愛因斯坦也是這麼想出他的...\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and how Einstein conceived of his theory of rela...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.97,0:35:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,父親 你相信有鬼魂嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Father, do you believe in ghosts?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.41,0:35:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,我不信有 人類的鬼魂\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Oh, no, not in the human kind of ghosts.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.65,0:35:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,完全不信\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No, not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.25,0:35:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,但是 向上看 兒子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But look up, my boy,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.42,0:35:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,滿天都是鬼魂\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and see a sky full of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.69,0:35:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,你如果去過黑洞還能活著回來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If you could survive the trip into a black hole,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.76,0:36:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,你可能會發現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}you might emerge in another place
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.33,0:36:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我們宇宙中的其他時間和空間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and time in our own universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.83,0:36:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,先不提 相對論的第一條戒律\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}circumventing the first commandment of relativity...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.00,0:36:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,汝不可超越光速\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}thou shalt not travel faster than light.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.60,0:36:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,太空中沒有什麼速度可以比光速快\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Nothing can move through space faster than light.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.87,0:36:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,但太空並不空曠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But space is not mere emptiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.34,0:36:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,空間可以延伸 收縮  被扭曲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Its properties can stretch and shrink and can be deformed.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.95,0:36:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,那樣的話 時間也會被扭曲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And when that happens, time is deformed, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.35,0:36:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,愛因斯坦發現 空間和時間 只是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Einstein discovered that spaceand time are just two aspects
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.13,0:36:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,一個事物的兩個方面  時空\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the same thing, spacetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.36,0:36:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,時空本身可以被任意彎曲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Spacetime itself can deform enough
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.96,0:36:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,用任意速度帶你去任意地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to carry you anywhere at any speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.30,0:36:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,黑洞可能是不同宇宙間的隧道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Black holes may very well be tunnels through the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.09,0:37:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,通過這種星際間的交通系統 你可以\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}On this intergalactic subway system, you could travel
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.89,0:37:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,達到時空的最遠端\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to the farthest reaches of spacetime,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.99,0:37:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,或許其他更驚人的地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or you might arrive in someplace even more amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.00,0:37:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,或許是個完全不一樣的宇宙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We might find ourselves in an altogether different universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.50,0:37:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,但是一個黑洞怎麼能容納整個宇宙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But how can a whole universe fit inside of a black hole,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.34,0:37:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,黑洞只是我們宇宙中的很小一部分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which is only a small part of our universe?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.08,0:37:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,這又是一個時空變出的戲法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's another magic trick of spacetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.18,0:37:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,黑洞無與倫比的引力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The phenomenal gravity of a black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.12,0:37:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,可以將整個宇宙的空間扭曲並塞進去\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}can warp the space of an entire universe inside it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.36,0:37:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我們現在受到的引力 或許很強\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our local gravity might be a drag to us,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.76,0:37:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,但卻無法和\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but it's really feeble compared
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.47,0:37:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,萎縮恆星內部的引力 相提並論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with what goes on inside a collapsed star.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.93,0:37:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,據我們所知\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}As far as we know,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.04,0:37:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,當超大恆星萎縮成黑洞時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when a giant star collapses to make a black hole,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.77,0:37:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,中心產生極大的密度和壓力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the extreme density and pressure at the center
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.54,0:38:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,如同誕生宇宙的大爆炸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}mimic the Big Bang, which gave rise to our universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.31,0:38:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,於是黑洞內誕生了一個宇宙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And a universe inside a black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.05,0:38:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,這宇宙可能會產生它自己的黑洞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}might give rise to its own black holes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.62,0:38:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,這些黑洞 又會產生其他的宇宙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And those could lead to other universes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.39,0:38:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,或許我們的宇宙就是如此\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Maybe that's how our cosmos came to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.97,0:38:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,眾所周知\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For all we know,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.81,0:38:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你想知道黑洞裏面有什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}if you want to see what it's like inside a black hole,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.08,0:38:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,只要看看四周\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}just look around you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.99,0:38:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,威廉·赫歇爾發現了 太陽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}William Herschel went on to discover that the sun
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.66,0:38:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,帶著它的行星們 在銀河系中運行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and its planets are moving through the Milky Way.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.16,0:38:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,他的兒子有什麼成就呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And whatever became of his son John?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.76,0:38:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,他成為了一位偉大的科學家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He grew up to become a great scientist.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.77,0:38:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,在他父親的基礎上 他所得出的外太空觀測結果\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}His deep-space observations built on those of his father
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.44,0:38:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,成為了星系標準目錄的依據\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to become the basis for the standard catalog of galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.10,0:39:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,沿用至今\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we use today.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.04,0:39:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,當威廉身體不好時  約翰陪著他\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When William was in failing health, John stayed with him
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.28,0:39:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,在望遠鏡旁 度過長夜\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}through the long nights at his telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.28,0:39:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,幫他觀測恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to help him sweep the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.11,0:39:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,父親過世後 約翰寫下墓誌銘\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And when his father died, John wrote his epitaph...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.12,0:39:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,他推倒天堂的圍牆\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}"He broke through the walls of heaven."
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.80,0:39:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,約翰經常緬懷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}John often reminisced
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.47,0:39:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,與他父親度過的那些夏日夜晚\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}about those summer nights with his father.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.54,0:39:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,這或許就是為何 他要尋找保存過去的方法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Maybe that's why he sought a way to preserve the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.71,0:39:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,約翰 赫歇爾 是一種展現形式的時間旅行的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}John Herschel was one of the founders
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.48,0:39:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,創始人之一\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of a new form of time travel,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.55,0:39:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,一種保留光線和記憶的辦法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a means to capture light and memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.42,0:39:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,他為它選擇了一個名字\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He actually coined a word for it,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.89,0:39:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,攝影\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}photography.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.16,0:39:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,你這麼想\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When you think about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.73,0:39:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,攝影是時間旅行的一種形式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}photography is a form of time travel.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.57,0:40:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,幾百年前的人注視著我們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This man is staring at us from across the centuries...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.07,0:40:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,光線勾勒出的鬼魂\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a ghost preserved by light.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.50,0:40:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,不難想像 在不遠的未來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's not hard to imagine that in the near future,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.34,0:40:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我們可以保留過去\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we'll be able to capture the past
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.11,0:40:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,以三維立體的形式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in all three dimensions.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.34,0:40:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我們可以走進一段記憶\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We'll be able to step inside a memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.42,0:40:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,或許不能回到過去的時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It may not be possible to travel backward in time,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.26,0:40:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,但可能 有一天 可以將過去帶來現在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but perhaps, one day, we can bring the past to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.79,0:40:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,這是我過去的一刻\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Here's a moment from my past.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.03,0:40:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,就像約翰赫歇爾\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Like John Herschel,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.53,0:40:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我記得幼年的我\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I'm remembering a younger version of myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.37,0:40:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,1975年12月20號\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}December 20, 1975.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.97,0:40:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,紐約的一個雪天\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A snowy day in Ithaca, New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.47,0:40:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,生命旅程的一個拐點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A branchpoint on the road that brought me
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.78,0:40:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,讓我有機會站在這裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to this moment with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.71,0:40:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,那天我遇到了卡爾·塞根\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was the day I met Carl Sagan.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.32,0:40:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,就如同天空中那些星星的鬼魂\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Reminds me of those ghost stars in the sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.06,0:41:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,即使已經消亡 但星光依然照耀我們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}you know, the ones that still shine their light upon us long after they're gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.08,0:41:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,中文翻譯：@SaltyEggPain
